00:00:00.256 --> 00:00:03.584
<b>One part of efficient lifting is a moderate controlled pace.</b>

00:00:04.096 --> 00:00:07.280
<b>This enables your body to recruit the large muscles of your back,</b>

00:00:07.512 --> 00:00:08.568
<b>core and legs.</b>

00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:13.056
<b>Lifting too fast can concentrate force on your arms or low back.</b>

00:00:13.824 --> 00:00:14.848
<b>Lifting too slow</b>

00:00:15.104 --> 00:00:16.004
<b>fatigues muscles</b>

00:00:16.128 --> 00:00:17.576
<b>and can be very uncomfortable.</b>

00:00:18.176 --> 00:00:19.200
<b>For maximum strength</b>

00:00:19.456 --> 00:00:20.480
<b>and minimum stress,</b>

00:00:20.736 --> 00:00:22.292
<b>lift at a moderate pace,</b>

00:00:22.478 --> 00:00:23.833
<b>and exhale while you lift.</b>

